The paper proposes a new representation of time series data using latent patterns and membership weights, which is optimized using stochastic coordinate descent. This approach is aimed at improving classification accuracy and is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data science (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
